x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Despite the known u=
nknowns in this debate, each campaign=E2=80=99s arguments are fairly circum=
scribed. Biden will portray his opponent as an insurrectionist, a felon who=
 is running to avoid a prison term, and a threat to women&#39;s rights. Tru=
mp, of course, will go after Biden on immigration, inflation, crime, and th=
e wars in Ukraine and Gaza, with the hope, according to his aides, that Bid=
en=E2=80=99s well-known defensiveness about his record will knock him off b=
alance. =E2=80=9CIf Biden is able to get away with a debate, and he doesn=
=E2=80=99t fuck it up, and Trump can=E2=80=99t get a lead, the election bec=
omes a referendum on Donald,=E2=80=9D said a former Trump advisor. =E2=80=
=9CAnd that=E2=80=99s not what Donald wants. If Trump is not in the lead af=
ter the debate, Trump will lose.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>In pursuing these argum=
ents, of course, Trump=E2=80=99s famous lack of restraint could risk making=
 him come
off as a madman. But some within his camp saw signs of newfound discipline =
at his rally in Pennsylvania on Saturday night. One advisor told me that he=
 seemed to be in =E2=80=9Chappy warrior=E2=80=9D mode, going light on the g=
rievances. <br/><br/>Trump also seems to recognize that the first 2020 deba=
te was a nightmare. His 145 interruptions resulted in a poll and momentum s=
wing for Biden, and one from which his campaign never recovered. =E2=80=9CP=
eople tell me I did better in the second debate,=E2=80=9D he=E2=80=99s been=
 telling people recently, according to an advisor. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s cl=
early heard that he needs to be Donald Trump 2.0,=E2=80=9D this person reit=
erated. =E2=80=9CThe question is, Does he say fuck it and not do it?=E2=80=
=9D<br/><br/>Trump, who views debate prep as a sign of weakness and a way f=
or others to take credit for his success, has been doing =E2=80=9Cpolicy re=
freshers=E2=80=9D with advisors like <b>Kellyanne Conway</b> and veep hopef=
uls, such as <b>J.D. Vance</b> and <b>Marco Rubio</b>. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99=
d rather it go well, and
have other people say he didn=E2=80=99t do debate prep,=E2=80=9D said anoth=
er Trump confidant. =E2=80=9CI think he needs to be patient and not take th=
e bait and not let things get to him. Let Biden talk, and let him talk hims=
elf into a pretzel, and let him go on and on and on. Initially, Trump will,=
 then he won=E2=80=99t be able to handle the attacks, and he=E2=80=99ll wan=
t to fight back.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Several advisors said that CNN=E2=80=99=
s plan to cut the microphones when there=E2=80=99s too much crosstalk, or w=
hen a candidate=E2=80=99s time is up, might help Trump by reminding him whe=
n he=E2=80=99s rambling and prevent any gonzo talk about thorny subjects su=
ch as January 6 or America=E2=80=99s epidemic of weak water pressure or the=
 threat posed by sharks. =E2=80=9CThe only way you make Joe Biden sympathet=
ic is to talk over him,=E2=80=9D a G.O.P. operative said. =E2=80=9CTrump=E2=
=80=99s weakness in this debate is if he gets sucked into debating January =
6 and who won the election. It=E2=80=99s toxic to suburban voters in Bucks =
County and Chester County in
Pennsylvania and Oakland County in Michigan.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>And yet, ne=
ither Republicans nor Democrats I spoke with envisioned an outcome in which=
 this thing didn=E2=80=99t go off the rails, at least for a moment or two. =
=E2=80=9CIt will be an absolute food fight disaster,=E2=80=9D the G.O.P. op=
erative said. =E2=80=9CIf they do some version of restraining, it probably =
lasts for the first 10 minutes, and then we see a food fight.=E2=80=9D Anot=
her Democratic operative said: =E2=80=9COverwhelmingly [the debate] is like=
ly to reinforce that people don=E2=80=99t want this, and they=E2=80=99re ge=
tting it, and they=E2=80=99re going to stay home instead of vote. Trump=E2=
=80=99s coalition is the easier managed of the two. He has the intensity of=
 real fanaticism, but that=E2=80=99s not enough. He needs that plus empathy=
=2E For Biden to make it about Trump is=
 a higher lift. Biden cannot look feeb=
le or lost. It will set off a Chernobyl-like reaction in the Democratic Par=
ty.=E2=80=9D <br/></td>
